# Architecture & Folder Structure

## Target layout (verified in repo)

```
src/
├── assets/{images,fonts,icons}/
├── components/{common,layout}/
├── features/<domain>/components/
├── pages/<domain>/           # route-level views ONLY
├── routes/{AppRoutes.tsx,routes.ts}
├── hooks/{api,services}/     # generic + domain TanStack hooks
├── context/
├── services/                 # api.ts + *Service.ts per domain
├── utils/validators/
├── types/
├── styles/
├── config/                   # env.ts — single env access point
├── providers/
├── test/
├── App.tsx
└── main.tsx
```

See `STRUCTURE.md` for the canonical reference.

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Owns | Must NOT |
|-------|------|----------|
| `pages/` | Route composition, params, page-level states, wiring hooks → UI | Direct HTTP, reusable cross-page UI, heavy domain logic |
| `features/` | Domain-specific UI (cards, forms, modals) | Route registration, API calls, global reusable primitives |
| `components/common/` | Generic UI (breadcrumb, empty/error states) | Domain API calls, domain types |
| `components/layout/` | AppLayout, AuthLayout | Business logic |
| `services/` | Endpoint paths, typed requests/responses | React hooks, JSX, toasts, navigation |
| `hooks/api/` | Generic `useApiGet`, `useTableDataQuery`, `useService*Mutation` | Domain-specific endpoint strings |
| `hooks/services/` | Domain queries/mutations wrapping services | JSX |
| `utils/` | Pure helpers, Zod schemas | API calls, React |

## Adding a new domain feature

1. Page → `src/pages/<domain>/`
2. Route constant → `src/routes/routes.ts`
3. Lazy route → `src/routes/AppRoutes.tsx`
4. Feature UI → `src/features/<domain>/components/` (when needed)
5. Service → `src/services/<domain>Service.ts` with `<DOMAIN>_API` paths
6. Hooks → `src/hooks/services/use<Domain>.ts`
7. Types → `src/types/` (shared) or colocated in service when API-specific
8. Tests → mirror path: `*.test.ts(x)` next to module or under `src/test/`

Do **not** create empty `hooks/`, `utils/`, `constants/` folders inside features until needed.

## Cross-feature reuse

- Shared across 2+ domains → `components/common/` or `utils/`
- Used once → keep inside the feature
- Never import `features/A/components/X` from `features/B`—extract upward instead

## Barrel files

Avoid new `index.ts` barrel re-exports unless the repo already uses that pattern for the module (`hooks/api/index.ts`, `services/index.ts` are established).

## Build output

Production build writes to **`build/`** (configured in `vite.config.ts`).
